This paper deals with energy and cost efficiency optimization solutions for 5G wireless communication systems with a large number of antennas and RF chains. It involves the use of massive MIMO antennas and millimeter wave technology, which are typically studied in the Information Theory (cs.IT) and Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) sub-categories. The paper also formulates an optimization problem and develops algorithms for maximizing energy efficiency, which falls under the Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-category. Additionally, the use of millimeter wave technology and optimization of the number of transmit antennas and user equipment number may also relate to the Multimedia (cs.MM) and Augmented Reality (cs.AR) sub-categories.
